Pygofer lobe
. Process orientation, ventrad; process basally edentate; process origin, medially on dorso-apical margin of lobe; process straight, narrow, acuminate (
Fig. 16F
), subapex bidentate, asymmetric, apex triangular (
Fig. 16E
); pygofer lobe narrowly merged with pygofer, constricted at base, lobe rectangular, apex dorsally rectangular, apex ventrally somewhat produced ventrad and posteriad; anterior apodeme short, dorsal (
Figs 16F, 16H
). apex of pygofer lobe shorter relative to apex of subgenital plate.

Valvifer 1
. In lateral view, about as wide as long; ventral margin rounded; anterior margin straight, dorsal and posterior margins sublinear (
Fig. 16K
). In dorsal view, merged broadly (
Fig. 16L
).
